# 🃏 Card Scanner — Pokémon & Yu-Gi-Oh

A mobile-first PWA that uses AI to identify trading cards and fetch live market prices.

## Features

- 📷 Camera scanning or image upload
- 🤖 AI card identification via Claude (Anthropic)
- 💰 Live Pokémon prices from TCGPlayer via Pokemon TCG API
- 💰 Live Yu-Gi-Oh prices from TCGPlayer, Card Market, eBay & more via YGOPRODeck
- 📱 Installable as a home screen app (PWA)
- 🌙 Dark mode, mobile optimised

## Setup

1. Deploy to Netlify or GitHub Pages (no build step needed — it's a plain HTML file)
2. Visit the app and enter your [Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com)
3. Your key is saved to your device (localStorage) — you only enter it once

## APIs Used

| API | Purpose | Key Required? |
|-----|---------|--------------|
| Anthropic Claude | Card image recognition | ✅ Yes (your own key) |
| [Pokemon TCG API](https://pokemontcg.io) | Pokémon card prices | ❌ No |
| [YGOPRODeck](https://ygoprodeck.com/api-guide/) | Yu-Gi-Oh card prices | ❌ No |

## Deploy to Netlify

1. Push this repo to GitHub
2. Go to [app.netlify.com](https://app.netlify.com) → New site → Import from GitHub
3. Select this repo, leave build settings blank, hit Deploy
4. Done ✅

## Files

```
card-scanner/
├── index.html      ← Main app
├── manifest.json   ← PWA manifest
├── sw.js           ← Service worker (offline support)
├── icon-192.png    ← App icon (add your own)
├── icon-512.png    ← App icon large (add your own)
└── README.md
```

> **Note on icons:** Add your own `icon-192.png` and `icon-512.png` for the home screen icon. Any 192×192 and 512×512 PNG will work.
